FL,327,320,120,260,000,100
PN,32602
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F326A1784299698
OL,3,CSon found guilty after mother left
OL,4,Cdying on floor for two weeks
OL,6,FParamedics attended the ground floor
OL,7,FRydal Street flat where the pair lived
OL,8,Ftogether.
OL,10,FThey found Veronica Irwin unconscious,
OL,11,Fsemi-naked and malnourished while
OL,12,Flying in a recovery-type position.
OL,14,FMedics initially thought Mrs Irwin,
OL,15,Fwho was described as being 4ft 10in
OL,16,Ftall and just over seven stones in
OL,17,Fweight, was already dead.
OL,19,FHowever she was discovered to be
OL,20,F"barely alive" and was taken to
OL,21,Fhospital.
OL,1,W{$~k4{$k4~sjw=                 G2/9
OL,2,W/.!+.!/*%/.!+,*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BBorder NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,327,320,120,260,000,100
PN,32603
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F326A1784299698
OL,3,CSon found guilty after mother left
OL,4,Cdying on floor for two weeks
OL,6,FShe died later that evening from
OL,7,Fhypothermia and neglected pressure
OL,8,Fulcers which covered more than a third
OL,9,Fof her body, and had caused sepsis.
OL,11,FDuring the trial, prosecutor Phil
OL,12,FBarnes KC said: "If only she had been
OL,13,Fmoved, or had had medical attention
OL,14,Fsooner, she undoubtedly would have
OL,15,Fsurvived."
OL,17,FThe prosecutor noted how there was
OL,18,Fonly one bathroom in their home -
OL,19,Fsuggesting that Mr Irwin stepped over
OL,20,Fhis mother every time he wanted to use
OL,21,Fthe toilet or brush his teeth.
OL,26,@tD@QOU
OL,1,W{$~k4{$k4~sjw=                 G3/9
OL,2,W/.!+.!/*%/.!+,*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BBorder NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,327,320,120,260,000,100
PN,32604
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F326A1784299698
OL,3,CSon found guilty after mother left
OL,4,Cdying on floor for two weeks
OL,6,FWhen opening the case to the jurors,
OL,7,FMr Barnes had said Irwin "owed his
OL,8,Fmother a duty of care".
OL,10,FAdding that: "The prosecution say that
OL,11,Fthis defendant, Stewart Irwin, is
OL,12,Fresponsible for his mother's death. We
OL,13,Fdo not say he meant to kill her. We do
OL,14,Fnot say that he was responsible for
OL,15,Fher falling to the floor in the first
OL,16,Fplace. We do not say that he intended
OL,17,Fto harm her.
OL,26,@oD@ZOUpD@VO]rD@NOU
OL,1,W{$~k4{$k4~sjw=                 G4/9
OL,2,W/.!+.!/*%/.!+,*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BBorder NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,327,320,120,260,000,100
PN,32605
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F326A1784299698
OL,3,CSon found guilty after mother left
OL,4,Cdying on floor for two weeks
OL,6,F"But he lived with her in a small two-
OL,7,Fbedroom flat. The bathroom she was
OL,8,Flying in was the only one in the flat.
OL,9,FHe must have been stepping over her
OL,10,Fevery few hours simply to use the
OL,11,Ftoilet or brush his teeth."
OL,13,FIrwin denied manslaughter by gross
OL,14,Fnegligence and opted not to give
OL,15,Fevidence during his trial.
OL,17,FHe was convicted of manslaughter,
OL,18,Funanimously, by the jury.
OL,26,@nD@AOUsD@[O]
OL,1,W{$~k4{$k4~sjw=                 G5/9
OL,2,W/.!+.!/*%/.!+,*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BBorder NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,327,320,120,260,000,100
PN,32606
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F326A1784299698
OL,3,CSon found guilty after mother left
OL,4,Cdying on floor for two weeks
OL,6,FIrwin told others, including the 999
OL,7,Fcall handler and police, that he was
OL,8,Fhis mother's carer.
OL,10,FJurors heard that during the fortnight
OL,11,Fin which she lay on the bathroom door,
OL,12,FIrwin made nine separate visits to a
OL,13,Fnearby shop to buy bottles of strong
OL,14,Fcider.
OL,16,FOn both the 19th and 24th July he
OL,17,Fwithdrew cash from his mother's bank
OL,18,Faccount.
OL,1,W{$~k4{$k4~sjw=                 G6/9
OL,2,W/.!+.!/*%/.!+,*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BBorder NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,327,320,120,260,000,100
PN,32607
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F326A1784299698
OL,3,CSon found guilty after mother left
OL,4,Cdying on floor for two weeks
OL,6,FJurors heard how Irwin had previously
OL,7,Fbeen interviewed by a clinical
OL,8,Fpsychologist. He told the psychologist
OL,9,Fhe had "tried to help" his mother who,
OL,10,Fhe claimed, had "repeatedly refused"
OL,11,Fassistance.
OL,13,FThat same psychologist found no
OL,14,Fevidence to conclude that Irwin lacked
OL,15,Fdecision-making capacity or that Irwin
OL,16,Fhad any defects in his ability to make
OL,17,Findependent decisions.
OL,26,@qD@HOUqD@VO]rD@QOUrD@dO]
OL,1,W{$~k4{$k4~sjw=                 G7/9
OL,2,W/.!+.!/*%/.!+,*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BBorder NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,327,320,120,260,000,100
PN,32608
SC,0008
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F326A1784299698
OL,3,CSon found guilty after mother left
OL,4,Cdying on floor for two weeks
OL,6,FAfter hearing evidence over the course
OL,7,Fof around a week, jurors found Irwin
OL,8,Fguilty, unanimously, of manslaughter.
OL,9,FTheir verdict was delivered around two
OL,10,Fhours after they retired to start
OL,11,Fdeliberating.
OL,13,FIn the court dock, Irwin, who wearing
OL,14,Fa long-sleeved checked shirt and light
OL,15,Fblue jeans, showed no emotion as the
OL,16,Fverdict was announced.
OL,18,FTrial judge Mr Justice Bright
OL,19,Fadjourned the case for preparation of
OL,20,Fa probation service pre-sentence
OL,21,Freport.
OL,1,W{$~k4{$k4~sjw=                 G8/9
OL,2,W/.!+.!/*%/.!+,*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
